WEBVTT

00:00.084 --> 00:01.651
<i>Previous on "Suits"...</i>

00:01.785 --> 00:03.852
I put Gallo away
for racketeering.

00:04.609 --> 00:06.209
But that's not what
he really did.

00:06.244 --> 00:07.477
What are you talking about?

00:07.512 --> 00:10.113
We had him for conspiracy
to commit murder,

00:10.148 --> 00:11.648
and the police let the tape

00:11.683 --> 00:13.917
of that bastard admitting
that he did it

00:13.952 --> 00:15.919
out of the chain of custody
for 20 minutes.

00:15.954 --> 00:17.687
You had an alibi witness,

00:17.722 --> 00:19.362
and your public defender
let her get away?

00:19.391 --> 00:20.657
That's what I've been saying!

00:20.692 --> 00:21.991
I didn't have
an alibi witness.

00:22.027 --> 00:23.927
I had a no-show who
vanished into thin air.

00:23.962 --> 00:25.439
Well, you could've
asked for postponement

00:25.463 --> 00:26.829
to have time to find her.

00:26.865 --> 00:28.631
And I would have,
except for one thing:

00:28.667 --> 00:30.311
when I pressed her as to what
the two of them were doing

00:30.335 --> 00:31.479
at the time of those murders,

00:31.503 --> 00:33.169
she admitted they
were both on meth.

00:33.204 --> 00:34.637
<i>Gallo's filing came back,</i>

00:34.673 --> 00:36.617
and it needs to be filed by
his attorney of record.

00:36.641 --> 00:38.675
You want me to represent
that animal?

00:38.710 --> 00:39.676
Kind of funny, isn't it?

00:39.711 --> 00:40.977
You fighting to get me out

00:41.012 --> 00:42.912
when you fought so hard
to put me away.

00:42.948 --> 00:44.314
It makes me sick
to my stomach,

00:44.349 --> 00:46.115
but you're gonna give me
something in return.

00:46.151 --> 00:48.318
Not only are you gonna
keep your hands off Mike,

00:48.353 --> 00:50.219
you're gonna be his
personal protector in here.

00:50.255 --> 00:51.455
You kept my wife
out of prison.

00:51.489 --> 00:53.323
As far as I'm concerned,
that makes us square.

00:53.358 --> 00:54.324
<i>Harvey and Mike did it,</i>

00:54.359 --> 00:55.992
which means Mike's coming home.

00:56.027 --> 00:57.560
Oh, my God.

00:57.596 --> 00:58.761
Joshua called.

00:58.797 --> 01:00.163
He's coming to town tomorrow.

01:00.198 --> 01:01.164
Are you gonna
break up with him?

01:01.199 --> 01:02.265
I don't know.

01:06.471 --> 01:08.471
I really appreciate
you doing this.

01:08.506 --> 01:11.341
If you weren't with me,

01:11.376 --> 01:13.343
I can't imagine how I'd handle

01:13.378 --> 01:15.912
whether or not Tara is
breaking up with Joshua.

01:15.947 --> 01:18.314
Joshua--what is he?

01:18.350 --> 01:19.983
Lord of the Kingdom
of Dicken-stein,

01:20.018 --> 01:24.153
reigning over his subjects from
high atop Douche Mountain?

01:24.189 --> 01:25.688
Anyway, thanks for being here.

01:25.724 --> 01:27.101
Aside from Tara, you're the most
important woman

01:27.125 --> 01:28.324
in my entire life.

01:28.360 --> 01:30.326
Oh, my God, Louis.

01:30.362 --> 01:33.162
Mudding is...

01:33.198 --> 01:36.099
amazing.

01:36.134 --> 01:38.368
I actually just fell asleep
for the last half hour.

01:38.403 --> 01:39.669
Goddamn it, Donna.

01:39.704 --> 01:41.182
I didn't bring you here
so you could fall asleep

01:41.206 --> 01:42.416
while I'm pouring my heart out.

01:42.440 --> 01:44.073
You're the most selfish
woman I ever met.

01:44.109 --> 01:46.087
I thought you just told me
I was the most important

01:46.111 --> 01:48.311
non-Tara woman in your life.

01:48.346 --> 01:50.179
Wait a second.
I thought you just fell asleep.

01:50.215 --> 01:51.581
And for the last
thirty seconds,

01:51.616 --> 01:54.183
have you been mad at me
or upset about Joshua?

01:54.219 --> 01:55.618
Holy shit, you're a genius.

01:55.654 --> 01:58.054
Which is why when we get
back to the office,

01:58.089 --> 02:02.025
you're reconciling everyone's
billings for the last six weeks.

02:02.060 --> 02:03.793
Oh, Donna, that is
the worst form of torture

02:03.828 --> 02:04.927
I can go through.

02:04.963 --> 02:06.562
No, Louis, the worst
form of torture

02:06.598 --> 02:08.464
is what you'll do if you
don't have something

02:08.500 --> 02:10.699
to occupy your mind.

02:10.735 --> 02:12.235
Oh, my God, you're right.

02:12.270 --> 02:13.569
I don't care what the cost

02:13.605 --> 02:15.571
or that I'm entirely naked
underneath this mud.

02:15.607 --> 02:16.873
I'm getting us another hour.

02:16.908 --> 02:19.075
Louis, you are not moving
another centimeter

02:19.110 --> 02:20.410
until Renaldo comes back in here

02:20.445 --> 02:22.211
and puts that privacy curtain
back up.

02:24.582 --> 02:26.249
Oh, look who's here.

02:26.284 --> 02:27.828
I'm not supposed to get out
till this afternoon,

02:27.852 --> 02:28.818
but leave it to you to--

02:28.853 --> 02:30.586
Mike, sit down.

02:30.622 --> 02:31.622
Okay.

02:35.493 --> 02:36.859
What's going on?

02:36.895 --> 02:39.106
Cahill called and said there
was a problem with your release.

02:39.130 --> 02:41.409
It's not a big deal, but it's
just gonna take a little longer.

02:41.433 --> 02:42.732
- How much longer?
- A few days.

02:42.767 --> 02:44.167
Harvey, I informed on someone.

02:44.202 --> 02:45.312
If word gets out about that--

02:45.336 --> 02:46.602
You think I don't know that?

02:46.638 --> 02:49.605
But he pulled your deal
then reinstated it.

02:49.641 --> 02:51.074
It's gonna take a little time.

02:51.109 --> 02:52.687
Well, what the hell am I
supposed to do in the meantime?

02:52.711 --> 02:54.410
Sit tight, and keep
your wits about you.

02:54.446 --> 02:55.945
You made it this long.

02:55.980 --> 02:57.747
You can make it a few more days.

03:00.285 --> 03:01.517
Does Rachel know about this?

03:01.553 --> 03:03.920
Look, she didn't know it was
gonna take this long

03:03.955 --> 03:05.755
in the first place,

03:05.790 --> 03:08.157
and I didn't see the need
to tell her now.

03:08.193 --> 03:10.393
Do me a favor, and let's
keep it that way.

03:13.364 --> 03:15.431
Rachel, good morning.

03:15.467 --> 03:16.866
I was looking for you before.

03:16.901 --> 03:19.435
I wanted to say congratulations
on getting Mike out.

03:19.471 --> 03:20.970
I appreciate that.

03:21.005 --> 03:23.439
But we have some
other good news.

03:23.475 --> 03:26.876
We may be on our way to getting
Leonard Bailey out too.

03:26.911 --> 03:28.811
Did you figure out a way
to reopen the trial?

03:28.847 --> 03:30.313
I did.

03:33.518 --> 03:35.318
Rachel, this is good
in theory,

03:35.353 --> 03:36.619
but there's no precedent.

03:36.654 --> 03:37.887
Yes, there is.

03:37.922 --> 03:41.224
Turner versus
the State of Michigan.

03:41.259 --> 03:42.459
How the hell did
you find that?

03:42.494 --> 03:45.128
It turns out being
a paralegal for so long

03:45.163 --> 03:46.562
was a blessing in disguise,

03:46.598 --> 03:48.998
because nobody is better
at research than me.

03:49.033 --> 03:50.366
Great. Write up a declaration,

03:50.401 --> 03:51.912
and get it to me
as soon as you're done.

03:51.936 --> 03:53.669
And I'll get this thing rolling.

03:53.705 --> 03:55.872
Jessica, I thought I'd
be the one to do it.

03:55.907 --> 03:57.807
Rachel, you're not
a lawyer yet.

03:57.842 --> 03:59.075
I don't need to be.

03:59.110 --> 04:01.277
She's his public defender.
She'll do this for us.

04:01.312 --> 04:03.846
Listen to me--sometimes things
don't go exactly as planned.

04:03.882 --> 04:06.449
And nobody is better
at research than you,

04:06.484 --> 04:09.952
but nobody is better at dropping
the hammer than me.

04:13.525 --> 04:14.735
Listen to me, I'm gonna ask
you a question,

04:14.759 --> 04:15.958
and I need to know the truth.

04:15.994 --> 04:17.593
You know about this Cahill shit?

04:17.629 --> 04:18.894
What Cahill shit?

04:18.930 --> 04:20.541
Apparently Sutter wasn't
enough for that asshole,

04:20.565 --> 04:22.732
because he's been seizing
our assets left and right.

04:22.767 --> 04:23.878
You really think they
were gonna let her

04:23.902 --> 04:25.835
keep direct proceeds
from insider trading?

04:25.870 --> 04:27.281
I'm not talking
about direct proceeds.

04:27.305 --> 04:28.745
I'm talking about
everything we have.

04:28.773 --> 04:29.839
- What?
- Yeah,

04:29.874 --> 04:31.107
including money she earned

04:31.142 --> 04:32.887
before she ever got wrapped up
in that bullshit.

04:32.911 --> 04:33.976
They can't do that.

04:34.012 --> 04:35.211
Well, they're doing it.

04:35.246 --> 04:36.690
And I don't care whether
you do something about it

04:36.714 --> 04:38.481
from in here or when
you get out there,

04:38.516 --> 04:40.427
but you're the one who convinced
us to take this deal, Mike,

04:40.451 --> 04:42.252
so you better damn well
be the one to stop it.

04:42.254 --> 04:46.154
