05:13.943 --> 05:15.551
<i>♪ The greenback boogie ♪</i>

05:17.179 --> 05:18.513
Hey, Counselor.

05:18.920 --> 05:20.453
You didn't forget about me,
did you?

05:20.489 --> 05:22.355
Your hearing's
tomorrow at 2:00.

05:22.391 --> 05:23.556
I sent you the paperwork.

05:23.592 --> 05:25.458
Right under the wire.

05:25.494 --> 05:26.760
Cutting it close, huh?

05:26.795 --> 05:29.496
I said I'd get it done,
and it's done, Gallo.

05:29.531 --> 05:31.998
Now I'm leaving.
So soon?

05:32.033 --> 05:34.234
I thought you might want
to meet and chat strategy.

05:34.269 --> 05:37.370
My strategy is for you to get
your parole tomorrow

05:37.406 --> 05:40.573
and then burn your existence
from my brain.

05:40.609 --> 05:41.919
I don't think I like the way
you just spoke

05:41.943 --> 05:43.543
to your own client, Harvey.

05:43.578 --> 05:45.111
You better come through.

05:45.147 --> 05:46.446
I'll come through, Gallo,

05:46.481 --> 05:48.281
but you better remember
your part of the deal.

05:48.316 --> 05:49.949
What, protecting Mike?

05:49.985 --> 05:52.352
What does Mike need protecting
for if I'm cool with him?

05:52.387 --> 05:53.387
Save your bullshit.

05:53.422 --> 05:55.488
I know you know
Mike was informing.

05:55.524 --> 05:57.624
Yeah, I also know William
Sutter's going away,

05:57.659 --> 05:58.899
which means Mike's getting out.

05:58.927 --> 06:00.160
Well, he's not out yet,

06:00.195 --> 06:01.595
so while you're both
still in there,

06:01.630 --> 06:03.963
you don't take your
eyes off him.

06:03.999 --> 06:06.800
I'm nothing if not
a man of my word.

06:06.835 --> 06:08.601
Oh, and Harvey,
I don't want to stand

06:08.637 --> 06:10.236
of the parole board
wearing this,

06:10.272 --> 06:12.772
so bring me something
nice to wear.

06:12.808 --> 06:14.841
I was a 38 slim
when I came in.

06:14.876 --> 06:16.676
Now I'm more like a 40 reg.

06:16.711 --> 06:19.078
I'll leave it up to you;
you're the dandy.

06:22.284 --> 06:23.249
<i>This is Sean Cahill.</i>

06:23.285 --> 06:24.584
Well, Sean, this is Mike Ross.

06:24.619 --> 06:25.885
<i>What can I do for you, Mike?</i>

06:25.921 --> 06:27.098
You can tell me why the hell
you're going after

06:27.122 --> 06:28.521
Jill Miller's assets.

06:28.557 --> 06:30.234
I'm sorry, I wasn't aware
you were her accountant.

06:30.258 --> 06:31.424
<i>Well, if you don't back off,</i>

06:31.460 --> 06:33.059
I'm about to become
her goddamn lawyer.

06:33.094 --> 06:35.662
<i>- Excuse me?</i>
- That wasn't part of her deal.

06:35.697 --> 06:37.481
No, it wasn't, but I'm not
gonna let her keep

06:37.482 --> 06:39.082
her money she made
committing a crime.

06:39.117 --> 06:41.217
You're not just taking money
she made from a crime.

06:41.253 --> 06:42.497
You're taking
the salary she made

06:42.521 --> 06:44.120
from working at that company
for years.

06:44.156 --> 06:46.289
Listen, that woman got out
of going to prison.

06:46.517 --> 06:47.673
But every time they took
a position,

06:47.674 --> 06:48.840
they sold the other side

06:48.876 --> 06:50.408
to people who lost everything.

06:50.444 --> 06:52.388
And I'll be damned if I
let her live high on the hog

06:52.412 --> 06:54.346
while working people's
lives were ruined.

06:54.381 --> 06:57.515
Sean, I know about
your mother and Spain.

06:57.551 --> 07:00.919
But Jill Miller didn't
take her money.

07:00.954 --> 07:01.920
I don't care.

07:01.955 --> 07:03.255
I have the power to do this.

07:03.290 --> 07:05.891
And this conversation is over.

07:11.666 --> 07:13.532
Jessica Pierson.

07:13.567 --> 07:16.301
My secretary should've told you
I'm not taking new clients.

07:16.336 --> 07:19.037
I take it you know
why I'm here.

07:19.072 --> 07:21.072
I tried to be polite when your
protégé accused me

07:21.108 --> 07:23.208
of not doing my job
with Leonard Bailey.

07:23.243 --> 07:25.510
But I'm not gonna be told by
someone who harbored a fraud

07:25.545 --> 07:26.878
what a bad lawyer I am.

07:26.914 --> 07:28.747
I don't think you're
a bad lawyer, Georgina.

07:28.782 --> 07:30.916
I think you're a good lawyer
that made a mistake.

07:30.951 --> 07:32.751
And I'm here to give you
a chance to fix it.

07:32.786 --> 07:33.852
And how's that?

07:33.887 --> 07:36.554
Leonard Bailey's
alibi witness is dead.

07:36.590 --> 07:38.323
That doesn't mean
her testimony is.

07:38.358 --> 07:40.892
You want me to testify
to what she told me?

07:40.928 --> 07:41.960
That would be hearsay.

07:41.995 --> 07:43.328
It would be if she were alive.

07:43.363 --> 07:44.663
But now that she's dead...

07:44.698 --> 07:46.464
She's an unavailable
declarant.

07:46.500 --> 07:48.533
Like I said,
you are a good lawyer.

07:48.568 --> 07:51.603
And I'm not pretending I let
a solid witness disappear

07:51.638 --> 07:53.238
when that girl was a junkie

07:53.273 --> 07:55.340
and her story was
inconsistent at best.

07:55.375 --> 07:57.120
And it still should've been
presented to a jury,

07:57.144 --> 07:58.610
which is what we're
trying to fix.

07:58.645 --> 08:00.723
The only thing you're trying
to fix is your reputation.

08:00.747 --> 08:03.214
And you're not doing it
by smearing mine.

08:03.250 --> 08:05.784
Georgina, a man's life
is on the line.

08:05.819 --> 08:07.552
And I did my best
to defend it,

08:07.587 --> 08:09.521
but I have no obligation
to do it again.

08:09.556 --> 08:11.156
That's where you're wrong.

08:11.191 --> 08:14.893
My protégé took the liberty of
drawing up a sworn affidavit

08:14.928 --> 08:16.828
which states Maria Gomez
told you

08:16.863 --> 08:18.676
Leonard Bailey couldn't have
murdered that couple

08:18.700 --> 08:20.266
because he was with
her at the time.

08:20.300 --> 08:21.700
Now you can either sign it,

08:21.735 --> 08:24.903
or you lie under oath
that this isn't true.

08:24.938 --> 08:27.539
And believe you me, you do not
want to be on that stand

08:27.574 --> 08:30.375
lying to a jury
and have to face me.

08:35.948 --> 08:37.615
Donna, cancel all
my meetings tomorrow,

08:37.652 --> 08:39.585
and notify the parole board
that Gallo's ready.

08:39.619 --> 08:40.996
- Harvey--
- I don't want to hear it.

08:41.020 --> 08:42.087
Listen to me.

08:42.121 --> 08:43.700
I was there with you
when you put him away,

08:43.724 --> 08:45.234
and I wouldn't be able
to live with myself

08:45.258 --> 08:47.370
if I didn't remind you what you
said about him at the time.

08:47.394 --> 08:48.493
I don't need reminding.

08:48.529 --> 08:49.762
You said he was a sociopath

08:49.796 --> 08:51.329
who took pleasure
from hurting people.

08:51.365 --> 08:52.664
Donna, I don't have a choice.

08:52.699 --> 08:55.266
That was before you knew
that Mike was getting out.

08:55.302 --> 08:57.180
If you just string him along
for a couple more hours--

08:57.204 --> 08:58.937
Mike's not getting out today.

08:58.972 --> 09:00.271
What?

09:00.307 --> 09:01.539
Cahill called me.

09:01.575 --> 09:03.553
The deal's gonna take a few
more days to go through.

09:03.577 --> 09:05.254
And if Gallo even thinks that
I'm stringing him along,

09:05.278 --> 09:08.013
Mike may never get out
of there at all.

09:08.048 --> 09:09.347
I'll clear your schedule.

09:16.556 --> 09:17.989
Hey, I need to talk to you.

09:18.025 --> 09:19.302
Before you do, I just
want to say

09:19.326 --> 09:20.503
I didn't mean to put it
all on you earlier.

09:20.527 --> 09:21.804
No, that doesn't matter now.
Listen.

09:21.828 --> 09:23.039
You said that when
you got arrested,

09:23.063 --> 09:25.597
you turned down a deal
to turn on Sutter.

09:25.632 --> 09:28.133
I need to know exactly
what they said.

09:28.168 --> 09:30.201
I don't understand what
that has to do with Jill.

09:30.237 --> 09:31.569
It doesn't.

09:31.605 --> 09:32.845
It has to do with the fact that

09:32.873 --> 09:34.372
I'm trying to get
you out of here.

09:34.408 --> 09:35.473
What?

09:35.509 --> 09:36.619
I might not be able
to do anything

09:36.643 --> 09:38.276
about the money,
but maybe what I can do

09:38.311 --> 09:41.413
is make it so that you
can be with your family.

09:41.448 --> 09:42.414
No.

09:42.449 --> 09:43.559
- What do you mean, no?
- No.

09:43.583 --> 09:44.694
They're already going
after our money.

09:44.718 --> 09:45.917
I don't want to do anything

09:45.952 --> 09:47.196
that's gonna mess
with Jill's deal.

09:47.220 --> 09:48.965
Listen to me.
That deal is as solid as a rock.

09:48.989 --> 09:50.767
I wrote it myself;
they can't take it away from her

09:50.791 --> 09:52.535
any more than they can take
my deal away from me.

09:52.559 --> 09:55.527
But you need to tell me exactly
what Cahill said to you

09:55.562 --> 09:57.162
when he told you
to turn on Sutter.

09:57.197 --> 09:59.798
Nothing.
He never said anything to me.

09:59.833 --> 10:01.032
What are you talking about?

10:01.068 --> 10:02.245
I'm telling you
I've never spoken

10:02.269 --> 10:04.069
to Sean Cahill in my life.

10:06.907 --> 10:08.239
All right, I'm here.

10:08.275 --> 10:10.475
But I gave you seven days
to find that witness,

10:10.510 --> 10:11.976
and then you went
behind my back,

10:12.012 --> 10:14.212
so you better have a good reason
why you're in here

10:14.247 --> 10:15.647
asking to reopen this case.

10:15.682 --> 10:17.949
We do, Your Honor.
We found Leonard Bailey's alibi.

10:17.984 --> 10:19.717
What they found is
nothing but hearsay.

10:19.753 --> 10:20.952
What is he talking about?

10:20.987 --> 10:23.088
He's talking about the fact
that our eyewitness

10:23.123 --> 10:24.355
died three years ago,

10:24.391 --> 10:25.757
and Mr. Bailey's
original attorney

10:25.792 --> 10:27.525
is going to testify
on her behalf

10:27.561 --> 10:30.595
under the Turner v. Michigan
exception to the hearsay rule.

10:30.630 --> 10:33.064
That exception involved
a written statement.

10:33.100 --> 10:34.944
It is a written statement,
and we have it right here.

10:34.968 --> 10:36.468
That is not
a written statement.

10:36.503 --> 10:39.003
That is a bullshit affidavit she
cobbled together this morning.

10:39.039 --> 10:40.505
What did you just
accuse her of?

10:40.540 --> 10:43.274
I'm sorry, Your Honor, but I
find it decidedly convenient

10:43.310 --> 10:44.976
that they don't have
the witness statement

10:45.011 --> 10:48.046
written down on a notebook
or a scrap of paper

10:48.081 --> 10:49.848
from the same decade
that it happened.

10:49.883 --> 10:52.016
Well, we happen to find it
decidedly inconvenient.

10:52.052 --> 10:54.052
And Georgina Casey didn't
write it down at the time

10:54.087 --> 10:55.620
because she didn't do
an adequate job

10:55.655 --> 10:57.322
representing her client.

10:57.357 --> 11:00.258
Are you now saying that this
case needs to be reopened

11:00.293 --> 11:03.161
based on Leonard Bailey having
inadequate representation?

11:03.196 --> 11:05.263
Because that is a serious
allegation to make

11:05.298 --> 11:06.431
about a fellow attorney.

11:06.466 --> 11:07.765
That wasn't our plan.

11:07.801 --> 11:10.068
But if that's what it takes
to give this man a chance

11:10.103 --> 11:11.503
to prove his innocence,

11:11.538 --> 11:13.338
then it sure as hell
is our plan now.

11:13.373 --> 11:14.772
This is ridiculous.

11:14.808 --> 11:17.242
It may sound ridiculous,
but if they were able to get

11:17.277 --> 11:20.645
a successful attorney to admit
to a huge blunder,

11:20.680 --> 11:23.025
then I'm ruling that this case
should be reopened after all.

11:28.421 --> 11:29.854
Cameron, what are
you doing here?

11:29.890 --> 11:31.033
You know what I'm doing here.

11:31.057 --> 11:32.201
Are you out of your goddamn mind

11:32.225 --> 11:33.625
representing Frank Gallo?

11:33.660 --> 11:35.304
- You don't understand.
- I understand plenty.

11:35.328 --> 11:36.739
- No, listen to me.
- No, you listen to me.

11:36.763 --> 11:38.207
That guy was a murdering
piece of shit

11:38.231 --> 11:39.375
who should've been
put away for life,

11:39.399 --> 11:40.443
and now you're trying
to get him out?

11:40.467 --> 11:41.799
He's in there with Mike Ross.

11:41.835 --> 11:43.268
I don't care.

11:43.303 --> 11:45.336
Well, I do, because
like you just said,

11:45.372 --> 11:46.838
he is a murdering piece of shit.

11:46.873 --> 11:48.940
But what you don't know is,
I made a deal with him,

11:48.975 --> 11:50.108
and I'm not gonna break it.

11:50.143 --> 11:51.576
- Then I will.
- It's not up to you.

11:51.611 --> 11:53.178
Well, it will be

11:53.213 --> 11:54.913
when I play this for
the parole board.

11:54.948 --> 11:56.114
What is that?

11:56.149 --> 11:57.682
It's the tape we had
of him admitting

11:57.717 --> 11:59.984
that he murdered that man
that you shit the bed with

12:00.020 --> 12:01.653
and got excluded from evidence.

12:01.688 --> 12:03.566
I didn't shit the bed with
anything, and you know it.

12:03.590 --> 12:05.390
You try to bring that bullshit
to his hearing,

12:05.425 --> 12:08.026
I'll march you out of there
before you get to hit play,

12:08.061 --> 12:09.561
'cause it wasn't
admissible in court,

12:09.596 --> 12:10.773
and it's not admissible there.

12:10.797 --> 12:12.330
You tell yourself
whatever you want,

12:12.365 --> 12:13.998
but I'm gonna do whatever
I need to do

12:14.034 --> 12:16.100
to keep that bastard
behind bars.

12:23.752 --> 12:24.652
Talk to you a second?

12:24.687 --> 12:25.653
Of course.

12:25.688 --> 12:26.654
You were right.

12:26.689 --> 12:28.022
The whole time I was working,

12:28.057 --> 12:30.758
I didn't worry about what
Tara was doing with...

12:30.793 --> 12:32.893
him, which meant the first
time in my life,

12:32.929 --> 12:34.528
I finished the billables
in record time.

12:34.564 --> 12:35.963
And now you're
afraid to go home.

12:35.998 --> 12:38.399
I can't help wondering
what's happening.

12:38.434 --> 12:41.168
Louis, have you ever
heard of a jack story?

12:41.203 --> 12:44.271
- No.
- Well, it's time you did.

12:44.307 --> 12:47.374
A man gets a flat tire
on a country road.

12:47.410 --> 12:49.143
He sees a house in the distance.

12:49.178 --> 12:50.689
He walks up to the house,
and along the way,

12:50.713 --> 12:52.947
he starts thinking, "What if
they don't have a jack?

12:52.982 --> 12:54.181
"What if they have a jack,

12:54.216 --> 12:55.761
"but they want to charge me
for it, and if they do,

12:55.785 --> 12:56.862
"how much would they charge?

12:56.886 --> 12:59.086
$100, $200, $1,000?"

12:59.121 --> 13:00.654
- That's bullshit.
- Exactly.

13:00.690 --> 13:02.100
So by the time the man
gets to the house,

13:02.124 --> 13:03.602
rings the bell, and they
answer the door,

13:03.626 --> 13:04.826
he tells them, "You know what?

13:04.860 --> 13:07.094
Keep your goddamn jack."

13:07.129 --> 13:09.129
- That's brilliant.
- So you get my point.

13:09.165 --> 13:10.864
No.

13:10.900 --> 13:13.701
Louis, you have no idea
what's going on in Tara's mind,

13:13.736 --> 13:16.570
so the best thing you can do
is trust her.

13:16.606 --> 13:18.472
Because if you don't,
I'm telling you,

13:18.507 --> 13:19.985
you're gonna do something
that you'll regret

13:20.009 --> 13:21.775
for the rest of your life.

13:21.811 --> 13:24.545
All right, Donna.

13:24.580 --> 13:25.946
I'll wait for Tara to call.

13:25.982 --> 13:27.581
Okay.

